<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <h4>Sustainability</h4>
      <p>Within both our business and everyday lives we seek to make minimal impact through careful management of our actions. We use recycled products where possible, conserve energy and water use, ensure efficient local travel, reduce waste and recycle. We support the local economy - using services and suppliers with a similar ethos.</p>
      <p>Many of our lodges have wildlife feeders, attracting native species including red squirrel and pine marten, alongside information for guests about the ecology of the area.</p>

      <h4>Electric Vehicle Charging Stations</h4>
      <p>Craigard Lodge has a 7kW ‘Type 2’ electric car charging point for guest use. Local electric vehicle charging stations can be found via the site below: <a href="http://www.chargeplacescotland.org" target="blank" class="green-link">www.chargeplacescotland.org</a></p>

      <h4>Accessibility</h4>
      <p>Each Seasgair lodge is unique and characterful, as such we hope that guests of varying ages and abilities can enjoy a stay with us. Several lodges have downstairs bedrooms with en suite walk-in showers, alongside spacious living areas. The ground floor of Alltnacriche is fully accessible for wheelchair users, has wide doors and sufficient space around furniture.</p>
      <p>If you have any questions or would like to discuss specific requirements, please <a href="mailto:hello@seasgairlodges.com" class="green-link">contact us</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
